Service Management:
There are 65,535 ports in a system.
systemctl start <servicename>, Same for restart, status, enable, disable - to check service statuses etc.

nginx is front-end web server to host web applications.

http default port no - 80.
https default port no - 443.

sudo netstat -lntp  - list all open ports and which programs are using them.


Process Management:
ps -ef - process started by user, gives user, process id, parent process id.
pf -ef | grep nginx - gets nginx process details.
sleep 10 & - runs in background without blocking the screen.

kill <process id> to kill process
kill -9 <process id> to kill process forcefully

top - to show process info such as  cpu ram and memory consumed etc.

